OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FCloudy but dry in the north at
OL,6,Ffirst, blustery showers follow north
OL,7,Ffrom the morning. The showers will be
OL,8,Ffrequent and heavy with hail and
OL,9,Fthunder at times in the west. Strong
OL,10,Fwinds with coastal gales.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FBlustery showers will retreat
OL,13,Fto western coasts from the late
OL,14,Fevening. With increasing clear spells
OL,15,Fand the wind falling light, a patchy
OL,16,Ffrost is expected in the east.
OL,17,
OL,18,CMonday:FMostly dry with bright spells
OL,19,Fand a few showers west in the morning.
OL,20,FCloud and scattered showers spread
OL,21,Fnortheast during the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
